public class EntityBeheadEvent extends EntityEvent implements Cancellable
Cancellable event created by the DropHeads plugin when an entity is beheaded.

      public Entity getKiller()
      Get the entity that did the beheading. It is possible that this differs from getSourceEvent().getKiller() because it can identify non-player killers, projectile sources, etc., if configured. Use getSourceEvent().getKiller() if you want the killer as determined by Minecraft.
      Returns:
      the Entity object representing the killer, or null if no entity was responsible
